# SCM syntax highlighting & preventing 3-way merges
pixi.lock merge=binary linguist-language=YAML linguist-generated=true -diff

# M21 Phase 5 (#242): gofmt is byte-strict about LF-only line endings. Without this, a Windows
# checkout of src/Aer.Sidecar (Windows git's default core.autocrlf converts LF blobs to CRLF on
# checkout) makes `gofmt -l .` report an already-clean file as needing formatting -- found live via
# CI's Windows job failing fmt-check-sidecar despite an identical Linux job passing.
*.go text eol=lf
src/Aer.Sidecar/go.mod text eol=lf
src/Aer.Sidecar/go.sum text eol=lf
